{
  "texts": [
    "This methodology is similar to that in (Hofstra et al., 2020) and (West et al., 2013).",
    "Names that were not in these datasets, or were flagged as ambiguous in the datasets, or had significant disagreement amongst these datasets were classified as Unknown.",
    "Excluding Unknown, a significant share (around 80%) of the weekly active users (WAU) in the first few months after ChatGPT was released were by users with typically masculine first names.",
    "However, in the first half of 2025, we see the share of active users with typically feminine and typically masculine names reach near-parity.",
    "By June 2025 we observe active users are more likely to have typically feminine names."
  ]
}